Food for an obese child: do not take breakfast and take meat for dinner
Over a third of children between 9 and 13 years of age have overweight problems, 9% of pupils are above average and 5% are obese.
As current research shows, obese children come from families who have an unhealthy lifestyle.
This again shows the importance of the environment in which the human being evolves and the models around it.
In obese children's tables, for example, carcutry is 50% more common than in families with children of normal weight.
19% of obese people had dinner fries according to the survey conducted with awareness-raising "Obesity is not a coincidence"
In the families of small big sports is also not a habit, which is now the case of most schoolchildren today - only 15% replied that at least once a week the parents found the time for active movement.
Survey of 900 children
The survey took place during the last school year and involved 900 students from primary schools in the Czech Republic.
It was the second edition of "Obesity is not a coincidence", action supported by General Health Insurance and the company Unilever.
Since the beginning, more than 12,000 students have enrolled in the project from sixth to third.
One of the determining factors that cause a dramatic increase in the number of children in overweight, or even obese, is the absence of a correct diet and not enough exercise.
"Only half of the children asked to eat, for example, 5 times a day - breakfast - lunch - dinner - which is a basic principle of a good diet", indicates one of the results of the survey.
No breakfast and meaty at dinner
Specialists draw attention to the fact that a healthy development requires some basic details such as a family breakfast at the same time.
In the Czech Republic, only 23% of the students' families eat at the same time.
In most families each takes their breakfast alone.
And the worst thing that has been noted is that a tenth of the population does not have breakfast at all.
Breakfast, however, is the basis for a good daily diet.
The questionnaire showed that poor fries are more frequently consumed in the families of obese children.
Almost every student - without talking about weight - drinks sugary drinks every day (70 %).
More than 40% of the children asked regularly do sports, but for parents it is only half, 15%.
Prepare your diet
Another part of the survey allowed selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to prepare their own diet on the basis of opportunities offered according to their own taste and personal opinion.
"The preferences of Czech children between the ages of 12 and 15 are far from ideal in terms of healthy eating".
Among their favorite dishes there are lots of cakes, meats and sweets.
"The most alarming one is a great preference for sweet lemonade," is indicated in the results of the survey.
For lunch it is the pasta that took the first place right in front of the white meat.
Children at all did not want feculinates and preference for fish and vegetable meals was very low.
Health
The survey also showed that children are ready to change their habits from the moment they receive ad hoc information.
"In the course of a review of a group of survey participants who had completed the questionnaire after the awareness-raising session "Obligacy is not a coincidence", a determined willingness to move towards a healthy diet was assigned," the survey results indicate.
For example, the most important thing has been for sweet lemons because children have begun to give preference to drinking water.
Children have most often checked white meat and fish as their main dish on the questionnaire and would reduce sweet food and knedliky (Czech speciality of bread flour or potatoes).
