Velvet Students in conjunction with the choirs of Charles University
Festa Academica festival offers for the third time festivals that link the International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical part.
During the festival, 20 choirs of secondary schools and classes occur.
The highlight of the festival consists of two concerts orgnized on 17 November.
"The University of Charles has an important part in this festival."
"One of the choirs there is the choir of the Faculty of Education and Humanities, in the committee of the festival is the rector Vaclav Hampl," says the head of the organizing team Jakub Calou.
The highlight of the festival is the concert of the Choeur des lycées et classes secondaryes, which takes place with free admission on November 17 from 2 p.m. on the space in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
On the program there is the composition of the well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Celebration Jazz mass.
In the evening the concert "Students of Velours" takes place in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady, during which the choirs of the higher schools as well as that of Charles University occur.
The Festa Academica aims not only to celebrate with dignity the International Student Day and to commemorate the 22nd anniversary of the velvet revolution, but also to present to the public a high-level choir music and develop the creative cooperation of young people.
The principal organiser is the Union of Czech Awards in cooperation with Jan Kepler High School.
The whole project is under the auspices of Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague and Vaclav Hampl, Rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from 16 to 20 November in Prague and Pardubice.
The program also offers high-level concerts, msical meetings, student happening and other activities.
Interested parties will find all information on the internet pages of the festival www.festaacademica.cz.
