Thus was the work of the person of Cali who identified the body of Alfonso Cano
A Cali dactyloscopic has gone to history as the man who confirmed the death of "Alfonso Cano".
The work of these officials is crucial.
Last November 4 a typoscopyist from the CTI in Cali went to history as the person who confirmed the identity of the Supreme Chief of the Farcs: "Alfonso Cano", confronting his fingerprints.
Of the seven dactyloscopics who work in the local offices of the ITC, this week it was the turn of the "availability" of Eliaszar González, a man from Puerto Tejada who has been working for 21 years in the field of judicial investigation.
At the beginning of his career, González worked in the Chocó towns, where many times he had to spend more than five days in the forest to arrive at the place where the dead were to be identified.
In the year 2000 he was transferred to the capital of Valle and after having followed appropriate courses, he specialized in dactyloscopy, which is the study of frictional skin, i.e. palms and feet.
During the week of the operation against alias Alfonso Cano, Eliazar had been warned to take clothes with him for at least three days.
Something very big was waiting for him.
Friday night he left for Cauca in a helicopter in Palmira.
He knew that he had to identify two corpses and that one of them was suspected of being the man who led the oldest guerrilla in the world, so he was asked to take the map with the ten fingerprints of Guillermo León Sáenz (his real name).
But when he arrived with the investigation team at the body's site, he did not recognize it by his physical appearance, because it was very different from the one he had seen in the media.
He had no beard, he was dressed like a farmer in the area, without glasses and much leaner.
But the prints don't lie.
Accompanied by a galtonian loupe, ink, a predator and a lantern, Eliazar compared the fingerprints of the corpse with those of the map.
His eye did not deceive him: it was "Alfonso Cano".
That same night, the man from Puerto Tejada was the one who confirmed to the Minister of Defence Juan Carlos Pinzón that yes, he was the Supreme Chief of the Farcs.
Looking for the print
For a dactyloscopist from Sijín de Cali, the recognition that President Juan Manuel Santos made to Eliazar González in a press conference for the operation against "Cano" is very significant.
Many people don't know our work.
Dactyloscopy is an exact science, without margin of error, which can be crucial in solving crimes.
Apart from identifying corpses, dactyloscopicists support investigations for crimes such as theft and homicide, and confirm the identity of the individuals captured.
When captured, many offenders present false identity cards or do not have documents.
We take their fingerprints and search them in the database.
The researcher noted that in a case of flight he had to remove part of a wall from a house, because in that place the thief had backed his hand to get out a safe full of jewelry and money.
"The walls are difficult because they are not adequate areas to draw a fingerprint, but in this case we were able to get the full hand print and identify the offender who had participated in various flights," he recalls.
The prints may also remove or confirm suspects in homicide cases.
Recently a dead man was found with bottles of drink around him.
Through the investigation it was determined that a parent might be suspect of the crime and indeed a print on the bottle coincided.
Even if it does not guarantee that he is the murderer, it places him on the scene of the crime.
A ITC dactyloscopic explained that "the fingerprints of objects with chemical or physical reagents" are extracted.
When they appear, a bearer or a band is used to pick them up.
Later, the prints were sent to Asif, the database of the declines, or to the National Civil Registry.
"The problem is that there are still many undocumented Colombians," the ITC expert reported.
He explained that not everything is shown in the CSI television program.
As all that shines isn't gold, everything you touch doesn't become a print.
However, it can be used if the necessary confrontation is achieved.
