"This morning's evacuation at dawn has been repugnant and shows that Bloomberg is more interested in defending the financial interests than those of American workers," added the movement's spokesman, who accused the mayor of "not respecting freedom of expression".
"Occupe Wall Street" also indicated that they did not think to organize "great actions" for Thursday in collaboration with community organizations and trade unions to commemorate the two months of protests, which began on September 17.
